but is it also a connection

01:11:40.240 --> 01:11:44.788
between the figure of the woman
and the act of petrification?

01:11:44.788 --> 01:11:48.403
Thinking about the Donna Petra,
I'm wondering if Dante's also

01:11:48.403 --> 01:11:51.774
saying something about the
dangers of love or the dangers

01:11:51.774 --> 01:11:53.100
of misplaced love.
 

01:11:53.100 --> 01:11:54.920
Prof: Thank you.
 

01:11:54.920 --> 01:11:59.905
The question is about the story
of the Medusa and the part about

01:11:59.905 --> 01:12:04.260
the mediation of poetry to
conquer Medusa is clear,

01:12:04.260 --> 01:12:10.788
but the question also wonders
whether this has to do with,

01:12:10.788 --> 01:12:12.650
first of all,
the fact that the Medusa is a

01:12:12.650 --> 01:12:16.551
woman,
and also that petrification is

01:12:16.551 --> 01:12:20.869
the petrification of misplaced
love.

01:12:20.869 --> 01:12:22.529
Is that an accurate paraphrase?
 

01:12:22.529 --> 01:12:23.078
Student: 
&gt;

01:12:23.078 --> 01:12:25.412
Prof: Okay,
the answer is that's a great

01:12:25.412 --> 01:12:25.970
question.
 

01:12:25.970 --> 01:12:32.176
I sense there your awareness of
the Freudian reading of the myth

01:12:32.176 --> 01:12:37.444
of the Medusa as castration,
as indeed a kind of

01:12:37.444 --> 01:12:42.796
literalization of the threat,
at least, not castration but

01:12:42.796 --> 01:12:46.578
the threat of castration on the
male from the point of view of

01:12:46.578 --> 01:12:47.198
Medusa.
 

01:12:47.198 --> 01:12:53.060
I will take the second part of
your remark to explain also the

01:12:53.060 --> 01:12:54.310
first part.
 

01:12:54.310 --> 01:12:57.229
I think that this is a question
of misdirected love,

01:12:57.229 --> 01:13:02.045
but what Dante has seen--I
would urge you to go and read

01:13:02.045 --> 01:13:08.430
the poems about this lady Petra,
the lady of stone--because they

01:13:08.430 --> 01:13:15.181
are poems where Dante literally
engages in fantasies of violence

01:13:15.181 --> 01:13:16.788
against her.
 

01:13:16.788 --> 01:13:21.307
If I could get my hands on her
with a passion,

01:13:21.307 --> 01:13:26.930
unrequited makes him--it's
almost like a sort of sadistic

01:13:26.930 --> 01:13:29.140
coloring about it.
 

01:13:29.140 --> 01:13:31.399
I think it's clearly
misdirected love.

01:13:31.399 --> 01:13:37.364
What he understands though is
the kind of death that that sort

01:13:37.364 --> 01:13:41.180
of desperate love has brought to
