01:16:20.100 --> 01:16:22.898
did you find that significant
just going back to what we

01:16:22.898 --> 01:16:24.170
talked about last time?
 

01:16:24.170 --> 01:16:27.560
Prof: Of course,
this is fantastic.

01:16:27.560 --> 01:16:34.051
The question is I have been
talking about the fact that in

01:16:34.051 --> 01:16:38.720
Inferno Dante goes to the
left,

01:16:38.720 --> 01:16:42.738
seems to--which I also said
though that that is really very

01:16:42.738 --> 01:16:47.404
difficult to visualize,
so we say counter-clockwise or

01:16:47.404 --> 01:16:50.832
clockwise,
that his descent is clockwise

01:16:50.832 --> 01:16:52.328
in Inferno.
 

01:16:52.328 --> 01:16:57.149
And yet, I'm so grateful to you
for noticing this.

01:16:57.149 --> 01:17:00.969
Here in Inferno IX,
Dante actually goes out of the

01:17:00.969 --> 01:17:04.380
way to say that he turned to the
right and the--

01:17:04.380 --> 01:17:08.024
I don't have a position of my
own on this but there will also

01:17:08.024 --> 01:17:11.257
be--
well this is to emphasize that

01:17:11.257 --> 01:17:16.038
heresy is primarily the disease
of the intellect.

01:17:16.038 --> 01:17:19.190
You remember that I specified
that there is the will and the

01:17:19.190 --> 01:17:21.806
intellect, and the will is
always the left and the

01:17:21.806 --> 01:17:23.250
intellect is the right.
 

01:17:23.250 --> 01:17:30.037
I think that Dante is--this is
the point where Dante is

01:17:30.037 --> 01:17:31.420
sleeping.
 

01:17:31.420 --> 01:17:35.136
It happened to Homer
occasionally to fall asleep and

01:17:35.136 --> 01:17:39.510
this is the only time that you
have caught him dozing off.

01:17:39.510 --> 01:17:42.000
Thank you so much we'll see you
next time.

